WEBVTT

00:00.109 --> 00:02.248
Previously on "Finding Carter"...

00:02.273 --> 00:04.975
Baby, you do not look at all well.

00:05.000 --> 00:06.716
I've got it under control.

00:06.752 --> 00:08.167
You knew eventually it would come to this.

00:08.220 --> 00:10.587
The truth has to come out.
The truth has to come out.

00:10.639 --> 00:11.671
Hi.

00:11.673 --> 00:13.056
This is Madison.

00:13.091 --> 00:15.842
She's my friend from back there.

00:15.894 --> 00:17.010
Remember back with Lori?

00:17.012 --> 00:18.728
You could come and go whenever you wanted.

00:18.764 --> 00:20.513
Nobody was telling you what to do.

00:20.515 --> 00:22.682
- Don't you miss that? 
- Yeah.

00:22.684 --> 00:24.100
I guess I just try not to think about it.

00:24.152 --> 00:25.852
Well, she thinks about you all the time.

00:25.904 --> 00:27.854
- How do you know that?
- I've been talking to her.

00:27.856 --> 00:28.988
I don't want to be apart.

00:29.024 --> 00:30.523
We had a really great thing going.

00:30.525 --> 00:31.825
We should have it again.

00:31.860 --> 00:34.410
You love her. You two are so good together.

00:34.446 --> 00:35.862
I've been thinking about something.

00:35.864 --> 00:37.747
About why you're not feeling any better.

00:37.783 --> 00:38.998
I think it's about Lori.

00:39.034 --> 00:40.834
About her being our biological mother.

00:40.869 --> 00:42.619
I couldn't get pregnant.

00:42.671 --> 00:44.204
And we decided to look for an egg donor.

00:44.206 --> 00:45.505
They chose me.

00:45.540 --> 00:46.623
Lori told us the truth,

00:46.675 --> 00:48.875
and then things just started to fall apart.

00:48.877 --> 00:51.795
Like with Max and mom and dad.

00:51.847 --> 00:53.379
I hate that she's my mother.

00:53.381 --> 00:54.547
Please don't shut us out.

00:54.599 --> 00:55.882
It's okay.

00:57.185 --> 00:58.384
It's about Lori.

00:58.436 --> 01:00.220
She tried to kill herself.

01:02.791 --> 01:04.541
Hey. Morning.

01:04.593 --> 01:06.042
- Good morning. 
- Coffee?

01:06.094 --> 01:08.261
Mmm. Thank you.

01:08.296 --> 01:09.546
Carter come down yet?

01:09.598 --> 01:10.463
No.

01:10.465 --> 01:11.631
She didn't sleep.

01:11.683 --> 01:14.851
Her light was on all night.

01:14.886 --> 01:16.970
Every time I think we're
finally done with Lori,

01:17.022 --> 01:20.139
she manages to find a way to
worm her way back into our lives.

01:20.192 --> 01:21.641
Yes, she does.

01:21.643 --> 01:23.643
But I'm worried about Carter

01:23.645 --> 01:25.862
and why she didn't want to talk last night.

01:25.897 --> 01:27.514
She's probably in shock.

01:30.118 --> 01:32.906
No, I can't, I'm sorry.

01:32.931 --> 01:34.714
No, look, I've made up my mind.

01:34.739 --> 01:37.290
Okay. Bye.

01:37.325 --> 01:38.156
Who was that?

01:38.181 --> 01:40.078
Lori's doctor.

01:40.829 --> 01:42.495
He wants me to come and meet him.

01:42.497 --> 01:43.880
- Why? 
- Because they always try

01:43.915 --> 01:46.165
and talk to the family after
something like this happens.

01:46.218 --> 01:48.334
Well, she's not really our family.

01:48.386 --> 01:49.502
Yeah, I know, Taylor.

01:49.554 --> 01:50.981
That's not what he was saying.

01:51.006 --> 01:52.389
Well, then what was he saying?

01:52.934 --> 01:54.674
I think it's pretty simple, Carter.

01:54.726 --> 01:57.427
She's insane. She always has been.

01:57.479 --> 01:59.312
Okay, yeah, well.

01:59.347 --> 02:01.648
I think there's a little
more to it than that.

02:01.683 --> 02:03.066
You're not going, are you?

02:03.101 --> 02:05.685
No, I made plans with Max.

02:05.687 --> 02:08.488
He was always good to talk
to when nothing made sense.

02:08.523 --> 02:10.740
Yeah. Yeah, he's the best.

02:10.775 --> 02:13.076
All right. I'll see you later.

02:13.111 --> 02:14.861
Hey, Carter.

02:14.913 --> 02:17.030
Mom and grandma and I are
doing that charity thing

02:17.082 --> 02:18.915
at the country club tonight.

02:18.950 --> 02:20.080
Will you be there?

02:20.105 --> 02:21.971
Oh, um... yeah.

02:21.996 --> 02:23.496
See you there.

02:26.735 --> 02:29.536
Hey. Look who's here.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.905
What's the matter? You
look like someone died.

02:33.071 --> 02:33.907
Not quite.

02:33.959 --> 02:35.459
What does that mean?

02:35.875 --> 02:37.327
Lori tried to kill herself.

02:37.379 --> 02:39.413
- What? 
- They found her in time.

02:39.465 --> 02:40.547
I don't understand.

02:40.583 --> 02:43.083
She was fine, I thought
she was doing better.

02:43.085 --> 02:45.636
- Have you talked to her?
- No, and I'm not going to.

02:45.671 --> 02:47.754
- Why not? 
- Because I'm not getting

02:47.756 --> 02:49.089
sucked into her drama again.

02:49.091 --> 02:50.641
That is exactly what she wants.

02:50.676 --> 02:52.926
She's obviously sick.

02:54.680 --> 02:56.430
Seriously, if she had
cancer, would you abandon her?

02:56.482 --> 02:58.732
That is not the same
thing, and you know it.

02:58.767 --> 03:00.100
You can't even compare those two.

03:00.152 --> 03:01.352
It's obviously mental illness.

03:01.353 --> 03:03.437
You guys act like she
has control over this.

03:05.774 --> 03:07.107
Look, I know she's done awful things,

03:07.109 --> 03:09.276
I get that, but...

03:09.328 --> 03:11.361
I mean, she could have died, and you're

03:11.413 --> 03:14.031
acting like you wouldn't have even cared.

03:15.784 --> 03:17.784
♪ There you go ♪

03:17.837 --> 03:20.754
♪ There you stay ♪

03:20.789 --> 03:22.623
♪ Keeping low ♪

03:22.675 --> 03:25.008
♪ Never want to play ♪

03:25.044 --> 03:27.628
♪ You've been up and down, down ♪

03:27.680 --> 03:29.847
♪ You've been
low-low-low ♪

03:29.882 --> 03:34.935
♪ Pretending to not feel alone ♪

03:34.970 --> 03:39.640
♪ Pretending to not feel alone ♪

03:39.750 --> 03:41.909
- Synced and corrected by ChrisKe -
